Package: DGE.Tools2
Title: A function library to facilitate Differential Gene Expression Analysis
Version: 2.0.2
Authors@R: person("John", "Thompson", email = "john.thompson@bms.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a function toolkit to facilite reproducible RNA-Seq DGE
    analysis and improve TBio "branding" by standardizing several types of commmon
    plots. The functions can be grouped into four categories (DGE workflow, DGE
    plotting tools, mapping/unit conversion functions and a ggplot themepack.
    The DGE workflow functions include: Function Build_RSE which reads text
    files and builds a SummarizedExperiment object; Function runEdgeRNorm which
    normalizes counts and produces a SubsettableListOfArrays (SLOA) object; Function
    runVoom runs limma voom and lmFit adding additional data to the SLOA object;
    Function runSVA for detrending unknown covariates. A variety of QC plots are
    produced to evaluate data quality. The DGE Plotting tools are suitable for
    downstream analysis visualizations and include: profilePlot, volcanoPlot,
    comparePlot, plotPvalHist, ggplotMDS and JRT_heatmap. Mapping and conversion
    functions include: GeneSym2Entrez, EnsemblGene2Entrez, Entrez2GeneSym,
    EnsemblGene2GeneSym, countToTpm, countToFpkm, fpkmToTpm, Log2CPM_To_Log2FPKM and
    cpmToFpkm. Lastly, several ggplot themes are provided that make it easy to set
    up readable plots for both knitr reports and PPT presentations. NEW - Xpress2RSE
    will build a gene level RSE directly from Xpress.
